00:10:54,270 --> 00:10:55,950
Not a quince.
A quill!

266
00:10:56,350 --> 00:10:57,850
Right! A quail?

267
00:10:58,270 --> 00:10:59,330
[ Flutter! ]

268
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:01,630
A quilt!
A quesadilla?

269
00:11:01,990 --> 00:11:02,710
Ugh.

270
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:05,330
Aha! A quiche.

271
00:11:05,430 --> 00:11:07,630
Not a quiche. A quill!

272
00:11:08,070 --> 00:11:10,290
Nope, sorry.
All out of quills.

273
00:11:10,930 --> 00:11:11,970
Aw, shoot.

274
00:11:13,930 --> 00:11:15,770
[ Clucking ]

275
00:11:15,850 --> 00:11:16,570
Come on, chicken!

276
00:11:16,710 --> 00:11:17,750
Here, chicky, chicky, chicky!

277
00:11:17,970 --> 00:11:19,270
Here, chick, chick,
chick, chicky!

278
00:11:19,330 --> 00:11:20,350
Come here!

279
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:21,270
[ Bang! ]
Unh!

280
00:11:23,770 --> 00:11:25,370
[ Clucking ]

281
00:11:25,490 --> 00:11:26,230
Come here!

282
00:11:30,510 --> 00:11:31,330
No! Wait! No! Wait!

283
00:11:31,450 --> 00:11:33,230
Stop! Quit it!

284
00:11:36,650 --> 00:11:37,430
[ Ding! ]

285
00:11:38,890 --> 00:11:40,830
[ Panting ] Spike...

286
00:11:41,210 --> 00:11:42,690
to the rescue!

287
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:43,470
[ Warble! ]

288
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:44,770
Twilight Sparkle:
oh. Spike.

289
00:11:45,110 --> 00:11:46,070
I was calling out for you

290
00:11:46,150 --> 00:11:47,730
When you were turning
this place upside down.

291
00:11:48,030 --> 00:11:50,650
Aloysius gave me one of his
feathers to use as a quill.

292
00:11:50,930 --> 00:11:51,570
[ Poink! ]

293
00:11:55,250 --> 00:11:56,630
That's just great.

294
00:11:56,990 --> 00:11:57,570
Perfect!

295
00:11:57,690 --> 00:11:58,730
[ Door slams ]
sweet!

296
00:11:59,270 --> 00:12:02,230
I think I'll just, uh, finish up
the rest of my chores.

297
00:12:02,450 --> 00:12:04,370
Or did Aloysius
already do them?

298
00:12:04,630 --> 00:12:07,070
Oh, no, no.
There are quite a lot of them.

299
00:12:07,470 --> 00:12:09,470
Well, that's fine
because I can just stay up

300
00:12:09,490 --> 00:12:10,410
All night and finish --

301
00:12:10,970 --> 00:12:11,990
[ Snoring ]

302
00:12:14,290 --> 00:12:17,010
Poor Spike.
He'll come around.

303
00:12:17,410 --> 00:12:19,890
He's genuinely
a good, little guy.

304
00:12:23,910 --> 00:12:25,250
[ Slam! ]
Huh?

305
00:12:25,830 --> 00:12:28,330
Twilight Sparkle:
Spike, what is this?

306
00:12:28,550 --> 00:12:29,990
You said
this book was missing.

307
00:12:30,290 --> 00:12:32,570
Well, Aloysius found it
right where it belongs,

308
00:12:32,770 --> 00:12:34,030
But like this.

309
00:12:34,210 --> 00:12:35,550
How did it get this way?

310
00:12:35,690 --> 00:12:38,910
Uh, well, um, you see,

311
00:12:39,390 --> 00:12:42,310
I-I just didn't want
to disappoint you, and, uh --

312
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:44,610
Have you ever seen
a dragon sneeze?

313
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:46,470
I've seen a dragon lie.

314
00:12:46,910 --> 00:12:48,790
I'm very disappointed
in you, Spike.

315
00:12:52,590 --> 00:12:53,590
You set me up!

316
00:12:54,030 --> 00:12:55,910
Well, two can play
that game.

317
00:12:56,330 --> 00:12:56,910
Hoo!

318
00:12:57,190 --> 00:12:59,210
Not "hoo." Two!

319
00:12:59,390 --> 00:13:00,670
Ugh!

320
00:13:02,150 --> 00:13:04,250
Aloysius is out
to take my place.

321
00:13:04,270 --> 00:13:05,210
I just know it!

322
00:13:05,810 --> 00:13:08,170
I've got to stop him. But how?

323
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:13,490
[ Mouse squeaking ]

324
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:15,790
Ahhhhh.

325
00:13:16,870 --> 00:13:17,770
[ Zip! ]

326
00:13:18,690 --> 00:13:20,170
[ Squeak! Squeak! Squeak! ]

327
00:13:20,370 --> 00:13:23,230
[ Laughs maniacally ]

328
00:13:27,450 --> 00:13:28,270
Come along, opal.

329
00:13:28,330 --> 00:13:30,430
Let's hurry up and get
to Fluttershy's tea party.

330
00:13:33,990 --> 00:13:34,530
[ Poink! ]

331
00:13:35,270 --> 00:13:39,130
[ Pitter! Pitter! Pitter! ]

332
00:13:40,290 --> 00:13:41,110
[ Squeak! Squeak! ]

333
00:13:47,510 --> 00:13:48,070
[ Pling! ]

334
00:13:48,570 --> 00:13:50,630
So lifelike.

335
00:13:51,250 --> 00:13:54,370
And when Twilight discovers
it shredded up on her floor,

336
00:13:54,570 --> 00:13:57,710
She'll think mouse-eating
Aloysius is to blame,

337
00:13:58,150 --> 00:14:01,650
And I'll be number one again!

338
00:14:01,790 --> 00:14:05,250
[ Laughs maniacally ]

339
00:14:08,950 --> 00:14:10,510
[ Pitter! Pitter! Pitter! ]

340
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:13,250
[ Sproing! Snap! ]

341
00:14:15,690 --> 00:14:17,490
[ Squeak! Squeak! ]

342
00:14:17,550 --> 00:14:18,830
[ Whoosh! Boing! ]

343
00:14:20,750 --> 00:14:21,530
[ Whip! ]

344
00:14:21,950 --> 00:14:23,730
[ Pitter! Pitter! Pitter! ]

345
00:14:24,610 --> 00:14:25,170
[ Yoink! ]

346
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:27,170
[ Laughs maniacally ]

347
00:14:27,290 --> 00:14:28,290
[ Zip! ]

348
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:31,230
[ Laughs maniacally ]

349
00:14:31,310 --> 00:14:32,430
[ Smash! Zip! ]

350
00:14:34,170 --> 00:14:34,750
[ Zip! ]

351
00:14:38,890 --> 00:14:40,810
[ Laughs maniacally ]

352
00:14:44,510 --> 00:14:45,490
[ Zip! ]

353
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:47,710
That poor little
field mouse --

354
00:14:47,870 --> 00:14:49,550
Torn to Pieces!

355
00:14:50,110 --> 00:14:52,290
It must have been Aloysius!

356
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:54,350
You know, since owls eat,
you know, mice.

357
00:14:54,770 --> 00:14:57,210
What a terrible,
terrible bird!

358
00:14:57,410 --> 00:14:58,770
He must be punished!

359
00:14:59,210 --> 00:14:59,650
Right?

360
00:15:00,810 --> 00:15:03,210
Spike, I don't know
what upsets me more --

361
00:15:03,490 --> 00:15:05,850
That you deliberately tried
to set up Aloysius

362
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,050
Or that
you actually thought

363
00:15:07,110 --> 00:15:08,770
This pathetic attempt
would work.

364
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:11,390
You've let your jealousy
get the best of you, Spike.

365
00:15:11,670 --> 00:15:13,390
I am truly disappointed.

366
00:15:13,630 --> 00:15:16,530
This is not the Spike
I know and love!

367
00:15:18,410 --> 00:15:21,050
[ Creeeak! ]

368
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:24,450
She --

369
00:15:25,030 --> 00:15:27,190
She doesn't love me anymore.

370
00:15:27,270 --> 00:15:28,670
[ Blink! Blink! Blink! ]

371
00:15:31,050 --> 00:15:32,610
Twilight hates me.

372
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:37,150
And I'm cold, hungry,
tired, and lonely.

373
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:39,030
Could it get any worse?

374
00:15:39,070 --> 00:15:40,890
[ Thunder crashes ]
[ gasps ]

375
00:15:43,470 --> 00:15:44,930
I guess that's a "yes."

376
00:15:50,590 --> 00:15:51,270
[ Poink! ]

377
00:15:52,230 --> 00:15:53,070
[ Echoing ] hello?

378
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:56,110
Hello?!

379
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:58,450
[ Thunder crashes ]

380
00:16:01,630 --> 00:16:03,170
What is that?!

381
00:16:05,430 --> 00:16:09,070
[ Twinkling ]

382
00:16:10,530 --> 00:16:13,090
Wow! If this is what
running away is all about,

383
00:16:13,130 --> 00:16:14,590
I never want to go home!

384
00:16:14,810 --> 00:16:15,910
[ Zip! ]

385
00:16:15,970 --> 00:16:17,810
Gems! Mmm! Whoo-Hoo!

386
00:16:18,010 --> 00:16:19,930
[ Chomp! Chomp! ]

387
00:16:20,470 --> 00:16:21,510
[ Hiccups ]

388
00:16:22,150 --> 00:16:22,950
[ Groans ]

389
00:16:23,690 --> 00:16:25,330
Even if my tummy's full,

390
00:16:25,730 --> 00:16:27,390
The rest of me is still empty.

391
00:16:28,130 --> 00:16:30,390
I miss Twilight
and the pony gang.

392
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:32,770
But she doesn't love me anymore,

393
00:16:33,350 --> 00:16:36,870
So I'm better off here --
All by myself.

394
00:16:39,570 --> 00:16:41,470
Wow, it seems
to be getting warmer.

395
00:16:43,710 --> 00:16:45,270
This steam is great
for my complexion,

396
00:16:45,770 --> 00:16:47,470
But it's sure getting hot
in here.

397
00:16:47,950 --> 00:16:51,210
[ Rumbling ]

398
00:16:51,930 --> 00:16:54,830
What are you doing
in my cave?

399
00:16:55,050 --> 00:16:58,130
And why are you eating
my gems?

400
00:16:59,110 --> 00:16:59,490
[ Ptoo! ]

401
00:16:59,590 --> 00:17:01,250
Uh, hey, aboo.

402
00:17:01,530 --> 00:17:03,090
I didn't know
this was your cave.

403
00:17:03,210 --> 00:17:04,490
And I didn't know
these were your gems,

404
00:17:04,570 --> 00:17:06,230
But we're cool, right?

405
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:07,390
[ Growling ]
whoa, whoa!

406
00:17:07,570 --> 00:17:09,870
Hey, uh, we're like brothers,
you know?

407
00:17:10,250 --> 00:17:12,450
I mean, you're a dragon
and I'm a dragon.

408
00:17:12,810 --> 00:17:13,970
It's us against the world,
right?

409
00:17:14,070 --> 00:17:15,950
[ Growls ]

410
00:17:16,670 --> 00:17:17,470
Aah!

411
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:18,890
Uh, you don't scare me!

412
00:17:19,370 --> 00:17:20,190
So you're big.

413
00:17:20,550 --> 00:17:21,850
[ Growling ]

414
00:17:22,010 --> 00:17:23,130
Really big.

415
00:17:24,350 --> 00:17:24,870
[ Shing! ]

416
00:17:24,990 --> 00:17:26,730
And your claws
are super sharp.

417
00:17:27,170 --> 00:17:28,110
Tail...
[ shing! ]

418
00:17:29,050 --> 00:17:30,270
...extra spiky.

419
00:17:31,050 --> 00:17:33,010
But, uh,
you don't scare me!

420
00:17:33,270 --> 00:17:33,830
Ha!

421
00:17:34,110 --> 00:17:34,830
[ Fizzle! ]

422
00:17:35,470 --> 00:17:36,830
How'd you like that?

423
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:41,590
[ Roars ]

424
00:17:42,270 --> 00:17:44,670
Uh, I'd love to stay,
but got to go!

425
00:17:44,750 --> 00:17:46,090
See ya!
Wouldn't want to be ya!

426
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:49,670
[ Roaring ]

427
00:17:49,810 --> 00:17:50,350
Aah!

428
00:17:55,450 --> 00:17:56,290
Aah!

429
00:17:57,910 --> 00:17:59,730
[ Screech! ]

430
00:18:01,130 --> 00:18:03,330
[ Snarling ]

431
00:18:03,430 --> 00:18:05,710
[ Whimpering ]

432
00:18:05,810 --> 00:18:06,990
Aloysius: hoo! Hoo!

433
00:18:12,410 --> 00:18:14,930
[ Whoosh! ]

434
00:18:17,550 --> 00:18:18,670
[ Snarls ]

435
00:18:18,710 --> 00:18:19,730
[ Whimpers ]

436
00:18:19,870 --> 00:18:20,390
[ Boink! ]

437
00:18:22,170 --> 00:18:23,630
Spike, over here!

438
00:18:27,790 --> 00:18:29,410
Am I glad to see you!

439
00:18:29,670 --> 00:18:31,390
Hurry! Hop on!

440
00:18:33,450 --> 00:18:36,390
[ Roaring ]

441
00:18:39,990 --> 00:18:42,190
It's too dark!
I can't see!

442
00:18:42,410 --> 00:18:44,530
Hoo! Hoo, hoo!

443
00:18:53,670 --> 00:18:57,130
[ Roaring ]

444
00:18:57,330 --> 00:18:58,190
[ Sighs ]

445
00:19:04,690 --> 00:19:06,010
[ Screech! ]

446
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:08,530
[ Panting ]

447
00:19:08,610 --> 00:19:11,010
Spike, we were
so worried about you.

448
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:12,830
I was so worried
about you!

449
00:19:13,030 --> 00:19:14,570
Why did you run away?

450
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:16,890
I thought
you didn't need me anymore

451
00:19:17,250 --> 00:19:19,110
And that you didn't
love me anymore.

452
00:19:20,150 --> 00:19:23,110
Spike,
sure, I was disappointed,

453
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:25,230
But you are
my number-one assistant

454
00:19:25,350 --> 00:19:28,130
And friend,
and you always will be.

455
00:19:28,470 --> 00:19:31,250
It's just that sometimes
I need some help at night.

456
00:19:31,590 --> 00:19:33,510
I can't ask you
to stay up late.

457
00:19:33,650 --> 00:19:36,250
You're a baby dragon,
and you need your rest.

458
00:19:36,670 --> 00:19:40,070
Owls are nocturnal,
so I asked Aloysius to help,

459
00:19:40,330 --> 00:19:42,210
But not to take your place.

460
00:19:43,270 --> 00:19:45,470
No one could
ever replace you, Spike,

461
00:19:45,790 --> 00:19:48,450
Not even when you are being
a jealous numbskull.

462
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:50,570
I'm sorry, Twilight.

463
00:19:50,870 --> 00:19:52,610
I never should have
been so jealous.

464
00:19:53,610 --> 00:19:55,130
And I'm sorry, too, Spike.

465
00:19:55,410 --> 00:19:56,910
I should have been
more sensitive.

466
00:19:58,210 --> 00:20:02,590
And, Aloysius, I know now that
you weren't out to take my job.

467
00:20:03,290 --> 00:20:04,190
Forgive me?

468
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:05,090
Hoo?

469
00:20:05,850 --> 00:20:07,150
Me. Forgive me -- Spike.

470
00:20:07,630 --> 00:20:08,150
Hoo!

471
00:20:11,110 --> 00:20:11,890
[ Chuckles ]

472
00:20:12,190 --> 00:20:13,790
He forgives you, Spike.

473
00:20:14,030 --> 00:20:16,410
Hey, how did you guys know
where I was?

474
00:20:16,890 --> 00:20:18,390
It was your
ketchup-Covered feet.

475
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:20,490
Aloysius discovered
your footprints,

476
00:20:20,550 --> 00:20:22,130
And we followed them
all the way to the cave.

477
00:20:22,350 --> 00:20:23,630
Oh, yeah, the ketchup.

478
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:24,950
It looked pretty real, though,
didn't it?

479
00:20:27,770 --> 00:20:29,170
Uh...
[ chuckles nervously ]

480
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:33,670
I know princess Celestia

481
00:20:33,730 --> 00:20:35,490
Will want to read about
what happened today.

482
00:20:35,690 --> 00:20:36,750
I'm ready when you are.

483
00:20:37,850 --> 00:20:38,490
[ Ding! ]

484
00:20:38,850 --> 00:20:41,790
Hey, Spike, why don't you
write to princess Celestia

485
00:20:42,070 --> 00:20:43,590
And tell her
what you've learned?

486
00:20:43,950 --> 00:20:44,590
Really?

487
00:20:45,090 --> 00:20:47,090
Why, that's
a big responsibility.

488
00:20:47,610 --> 00:20:48,430
I know.

489
00:20:48,670 --> 00:20:51,190
But nothing my number-one
assistant can't handle.

490
00:20:51,370 --> 00:20:53,130
"Dear princess Celestia...

491
00:20:53,470 --> 00:20:56,150
"this is Spike writing to you
about my adventures.

492
00:20:56,510 --> 00:21:00,230
"This week, I learned that
being jealous and telling lies

493
00:21:00,350 --> 00:21:01,690
"Gets you nowhere
in friendship.

494
00:21:03,070 --> 00:21:04,190
"I also learned

495
00:21:04,290 --> 00:21:07,010
"That there's plenty of love
for every friend to share.

496
00:21:07,330 --> 00:21:10,350
So from here on out, I promise
that i, Spike, will --"

497
00:21:10,390 --> 00:21:11,510
[ Thud ]
[ snoring ]

498
00:21:11,610 --> 00:21:12,570
[ Poink! ]

499
00:21:17,330 --> 00:21:18,810
Oh, Spike.

500
00:21:19,070 --> 00:21:20,310
Hoo?
[ Poink! ]

501
00:21:20,710 --> 00:21:22,890
"Who?"
Spike. You kn--

502
00:21:23,090 --> 00:21:27,170
Ohhhh! [ Chuckles ]

503
00:21:27,970 --> 00:21:29,030
[ Tink! ]

